arts.ttl: Sheffield Wednesday 1-1 Leeds United (3-0 pens): Youthful Owls shock Farke's men
arts.sum: Wednesday took a shock lead on the hour mark, as captain for the night, and only outfield player for the Owls above the age of 20, Jamal Lowe, attempted to put the ball into the danger zone from a tight angle, but instead, the ball somehow managed to squeeze through the legs of Karl Darlow and trickle over the line. Ethan Horvath made himself a hero, saving two penalties to help guide a youthful team through to the third round of the EFL Cup .

arts.ttl: Horvath’s heroics stun Leeds as Sheffield Wednesday pull off Carabao Cup shock
arts.sum: Leeds were embarrassingly knocked out of the Carabao Cup by a callow shadow side fielded by the Championship’s crisis club Sheffield Wednesday after a dramatic penalty shootout. After failing to put away a side whose outfield players had an average age of 20 in 90 minutes, Leeds succumbed in the spot-kick lottery. Continue reading...

Celtic are currently preparing to send it into one of them, from a free-kick on the right. And one for Celtic moments later! Hatate crosses, Forrest heads goalwards, and Anarbekov turns over the bar! It was a good header, plenty of power on it, but right down the middle of goal and the keeper only needed to fling up a hand. Continue reading...
